Madagascar Releases Opposition Leader Accused of Bomb Attack, Midi Reports

-- B y   H a n n a h   M c N e i s h
-- 
2011-03-30T09:56:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/madagascar-releases-opposition-leader-accused-of-bomb-attack-midi-reports.html
Malagasy opposition party leader
Mamy Rakotarivelo was released on bail yesterday after 15 days
in custody, the Antananarivo-based Midi reported, citing his
lawyer Hanitra Razafimanantsoa.  Rakotarivelo, the leader of the party in Madadascar of
exiled former president  Marc Ravalomanana , was accused of trying
to assassinate President Andry Rajoelina by exploding a bomb
near his car.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Hannah McNeish in Johannesburg at 
 hmcneish@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gordon Bell at 
 gbell16@bloomberg.net  